### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = 

### 1. Sign Up User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "profile": {
    "name": "Test User",
    "bio": "This is a test user account"
  }
}

### 2. Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get User Profile (Need token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Update User Profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "profile": {
    "name": "Updated User Name",
    "bio": "Updated bio description"
  }
}

### 5. Get All Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Search Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=test
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Create Project
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "My Test Project",
  "description": "A sample project for testing the API",
  "type": "Web Development",
  "hashtags": "#react,#nodejs,#mongodb"
}

### 8. Get All Projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Get Single Project (Replace PROJECT_ID with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/PROJECT_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Create Checkin (Replace PROJECT_ID with actual project ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/checkins/PROJECT_ID/checkin
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Added new features and fixed critical bugs. Updated UI components and improved performance."
}

### 11. Get Project Checkins (Replace PROJECT_ID with actual project ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/checkins/project/PROJECT_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

